project_name: Tunnel from bathroom to bathroom 100 feet. Open a hole behind master bathroom and another one behind guest bathroom to tunnel in. Tunnel will go across under the house and connect to the kitchen sink on the way. Make another hole in the garage floor in front of the washing machine and tunnel over to connect to main line. Tear out all old cast iron and carry off. Replace with schedule 40 PVC. It will run out from under the master bathroom and tie onto the main line. Put in a new cleanout for the main and a new line running over to the main line in the yard. Put in a new backwater valve in 4 pipe. Run a new line for the washer/dryer and possibly a new vent and washer box. In bathrooms: install new P-traps and toilet flanges and reset all toilets. Note: All 2 and 3 PVC will be hung at 4 foot intervals with stainless steel hangers.
description: Tunnel from bathroom to bathroom 100 feet. Open a hole behind master bathroom and another one behind guest bathroom to tunnel in. Tunnel will go across under the house and connect to the kitchen sink on the way. Make another hole in the garage floor in front of the washing machine and tunnel over to connect to main line. Tear out all old cast iron and carry off. Replace with schedule 40 PVC. It will run out from under the master bathroom and tie onto the main line. Put in a new cleanout for the main and a new line running over to the main line in the yard. Put in a new backwater valve in 4 pipe. Run a new line for the washer/dryer and possibly a new vent and washer box. In bathrooms: install new P-traps and toilet flanges and reset all toilets. Note: All 2 and 3 PVC will be hung at 4 foot intervals with stainless steel hangers.

project_name: At 14513 Mowsbury Dr Austin TX 78717 we plan to install a new code-compliant in-ground irrigation system designed and supervised by a TCEQ-licensed irrigator (License LI0030033). The system will connect to the City water supply with a tested DCV backflow preventer and a master valve and will be divided into properly sized zones for turf shrub beds and individual trees using a mix of high-efficiency MP rotors and drip emitters. PVC main and lateral lines will be buried to required depth wired through conduit. A WiFi compatible controller with rain sensor will automatically adjust watering schedules to meet Austin Water conservation standards avoiding overspray and runoff. Zone layout precipitation rates and run times are based on site hydraulics and plant needs and all components will be installed to meet or exceed City of Austin and TCEQ irrigation rules. Upon completion the system will be inspected the backflow device tested by a certified BPAT tester and the homeowner instructed in controller operation and seasonal maintenance.
description: At 14513 Mowsbury Dr Austin TX 78717 we plan to install a new code-compliant in-ground irrigation system designed and supervised by a TCEQ-licensed irrigator (License LI0030033). The system will connect to the City water supply with a tested DCV backflow preventer and a master valve and will be divided into properly sized zones for turf shrub beds and individual trees using a mix of high-efficiency MP rotors and drip emitters. PVC main and lateral lines will be buried to required depth wired through conduit. A WiFi compatible controller with rain sensor will automatically adjust watering schedules to meet Austin Water conservation standards avoiding overspray and runoff. Zone layout precipitation rates and run times are based on site hydraulics and plant needs and all components will be installed to meet or exceed City of Austin and TCEQ irrigation rules. Upon completion the system will be inspected the backflow device tested by a certified BPAT tester and the homeowner instructed in controller operation and seasonal maintenance.

project_name:
Video diagnostics performed from the exterior clean-out identified approximately 60 feet of building drain with improper pitch. The issue begins about 2 feet from the exterior clean-out extending beneath the Master Bedroom Closet and continuing to the area beneath the Kitchen Faucet. The existing 4¿ PVC piping is back-pitched resulting in standing water throughout the full pipe diameter.

This condition occurs at the outlet of the building drain causing drainage issues that affect all plumbing fixtures within the residence.

The proposed work includes tunneling beneath the home to access and replace the affected section of back-pitched piping. The new piping will be properly graded and securely strapped to the underside of the slab to prevent future soil settlement and pipe movement.
description:
Video diagnostics performed from the exterior clean-out identified approximately 60 feet of building drain with improper pitch. The issue begins about 2 feet from the exterior clean-out extending beneath the Master Bedroom Closet and continuing to the area beneath the Kitchen Faucet. The existing 4¿ PVC piping is back-pitched resulting in standing water throughout the full pipe diameter.

This condition occurs at the outlet of the building drain causing drainage issues that affect all plumbing fixtures within the residence.

The proposed work includes tunneling beneath the home to access and replace the affected section of back-pitched piping. The new piping will be properly graded and securely strapped to the underside of the slab to prevent future soil settlement and pipe movement.

project_name:
TCEQ-Compliant Components:
* 1¿ DCA Backflow Preventer (In-Ground): Required by TCEQ to protect the public water supply from contamination. This device will be tested and registered with the city upon completion.
* 1¿ Isolation Valve: Also required by TCEQ this allows for emergency shutoff of the irrigation system without affecting the homes water supply.
* Two 1¿ Master Valves (One Per Controller): As per TCEQ code a master valve is required for each controller to help prevent line leaks or water loss when the system is off.

Irrigation Zones:
* Four Irrigreen Rotor Zones: These precision digital rotors map watering patterns for each turf zone reducing overspray and maximizing efficiency.
* Two Drip Irrigation Zones: Installed for landscape beds these zones use subsurface drip tubing with 12¿ emitter spacing to deliver water directly to plant roots.

Installation Details:
* Trenching: All piping will be installed at 8¿10 inches deep using trenchers or hand tools depending on site conditions.
* Controllers and Wiring: System will include complete controller installation wiring and testing.
description:
TCEQ-Compliant Components:

* Two 1¿ Master Valves (One Per Controller): As per TCEQ code a master valve is required for each controller to help prevent line leaks or water loss when the system is off.

Irrigation Zones:
* Four Irrigreen Rotor Zones: These precision digital rotors map watering patterns for each turf zone reducing overspray and maximizing efficiency.
* Two Drip Irrigation Zones: Installed for landscape beds these zones use subsurface drip tubing with 12¿ emitter spacing to deliver water directly to plant roots.

Installation Details:
* Trenching: All piping will be installed at 8¿10 inches deep using trenchers or hand tools depending on site conditions.
* Controllers and Wiring: System will include complete controller installation wiring and testing.

Cap and Abandon Old Line Gas line
New Gas Line Installation
	Connect to existing gas piping under the house.

This is only for the water heater gas line not the entire house. The gas line for the water heater is made out of metal piping and has become damaged and corroded. For this portion of the pipe we would like to re-route the gas-line around the house and used new approved gas material. For this work we would like to apply for a repair permit since we are only repairing a section of the gas line
